goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the states with the most and least number of capital cities and understand any regional patterns.

goals.question: What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the central tendency of the capital cities and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="lon", y="lat", data=data)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data)
    ax.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean longitude: {data["lon"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(data['lat'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean latitude: {data["lat"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
